    "88f614a4-60c9-4da2-a498-9a50ed699889": {
      "id": "88f614a4-60c9-4da2-a498-9a50ed699889",
      "name": "Critical Files to Create/Modify",
      "content": "",
      "type": "note",
      "parentId": "0b4b1874-027a-4b81-9918-1c126b9e6619",
      "childrenIds": [
        "50eb581f-5936-49fc-8e33-c6f54cd7a756",
        "64543b6a-c9aa-405d-a487-1ee117f0b455",
        "d21f0bc4-9c2c-48ce-8141-82ea0663de5d",
        "863d7fc5-d9cd-462c-b173-53d301c12f63"
      ],
      "prefix": "7",
      "metadata": {
        "createdAt": 1768038036243,
        "updatedAt": 1768038036243
      }
    },
    "50eb581f-5936-49fc-8e33-c6f54cd7a756": {
      "id": "50eb581f-5936-49fc-8e33-c6f54cd7a756",
      "name": "New Files - MCP Server",
      "content": "**Core Server:**\n1. `/mcp-server/src/index.ts` - Entry point\n2. `/mcp-server/src/server.ts` - MCP server setup with SDK\n3. `/mcp-server/package.json` - Dependencies and scripts\n\n**Free Tier Tools:**\n4. `/mcp-server/src/tools/free/outline-read.ts` - list_outlines, get_outline, get_node, search_nodes\n5. `/mcp-server/src/tools/free/outline-crud.ts` - create_outline, update_outline, delete_outline\n6. `/mcp-server/src/tools/free/node-crud.ts` - create_node, update_node, delete_node, move_node\n7. `/mcp-server/src/tools/free/tag-ops.ts` - add_tag, remove_tag, list_tags, filter_by_tags\n\n**Premium Tools:**\n8. `/mcp-server/src/tools/premium/ai-generate.ts` - generate_outline, expand_content\n9. `/mcp-server/src/tools/premium/ai-ingest.ts` - ingest_source\n10. `/mcp-server/src/tools/premium/bulk-ops.ts` - batch_update_nodes, multi_select_action\n\n**Infrastructure:**\n11. `/mcp-server/src/auth/api-key-manager.ts` - Generate/validate API keys\n12. `/mcp-server/src/storage/storage-factory.ts` - Adapt storage-manager.ts for server\n\n**Documentation:**\n13. `/mcp-server/README.md` - Installation and quick start\n14. `/docs/MCP_SERVER_GUIDE.md` - Comprehensive guide\n15. `/docs/API_REFERENCE.md` - Complete API documentation",
      "type": "note",
      "parentId": "88f614a4-60c9-4da2-a498-9a50ed699889",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "prefix": "7.1",
      "metadata": {
        "createdAt": 1768038036243,
        "updatedAt": 1768038036243
      }
    },
    "64543b6a-c9aa-405d-a487-1ee117f0b455": {
      "id": "64543b6a-c9aa-405d-a487-1ee117f0b455",
      "name": "Shared Package",
      "content": "16. `/packages/core/src/types/index.ts` - Export types from src/types/index.ts\n17. `/packages/core/src/utils/outline-utils.ts` - Copy from src/lib/outline-utils.ts\n18. `/packages/core/src/utils/tag-utils.ts` - Copy from src/lib/tag-utils.ts",
      "type": "note",
      "parentId": "88f614a4-60c9-4da2-a498-9a50ed699889",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "prefix": "7.2",
      "metadata": {
        "createdAt": 1768038036243,
        "updatedAt": 1768038036243
      }
    },
    "d21f0bc4-9c2c-48ce-8141-82ea0663de5d": {
      "id": "d21f0bc4-9c2c-48ce-8141-82ea0663de5d",
      "name": "IdiamPro App Modifications",
      "content": "19. `/src/components/settings-dialog.tsx` - Add Developer tab for API keys\n20. `/src/lib/api-keys.ts` - Client API key management\n21. `/src/app/api/keys/route.ts` - Next.js API route for key CRUD\n22. `/src/types/index.ts` - Add ApiKey, PlanTier, UsageLimit types",
      "type": "note",
      "parentId": "88f614a4-60c9-4da2-a498-9a50ed699889",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "prefix": "7.3",
      "metadata": {
        "createdAt": 1768038036243,
        "updatedAt": 1768038036243
      }
    },
    "863d7fc5-d9cd-462c-b173-53d301c12f63": {
      "id": "863d7fc5-d9cd-462c-b173-53d301c12f63",
      "name": "Top 5 Most Critical Files",
      "content": "1. **`/mcp-server/src/server.ts`** - Core MCP implementation, registers all tools\n2. **`/mcp-server/src/storage/storage-factory.ts`** - Bridges existing storage with MCP\n3. **`/mcp-server/src/tools/free/node-crud.ts`** - Most used operations\n4. **`/mcp-server/src/auth/api-key-manager.ts`** - Security foundation\n5. **`/src/lib/outline-utils.ts`** - Core business logic (extract to shared)\n\n---",
      "type": "note",
      "parentId": "88f614a4-60c9-4da2-a498-9a50ed699889",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "prefix": "7.4",
      "metadata": {
        "createdAt": 1768038036243,
        "updatedAt": 1768038036243
      }
    },
    "37c2360f-bf60-4ee8-9ca9-0c1df9b9fcba": {
      "id": "37c2360f-bf60-4ee8-9ca9-0c1df9b9fcba",
      "name": "Next Steps",
      "content": "1. **Validate** pricing with 10-20 potential users\n2. **Set up** monorepo structure for shared packages\n3. **Begin** Phase 1 implementation\n4. **Recruit** beta testers\n\n---",
      "type": "note",
      "parentId": "0b4b1874-027a-4b81-9918-1c126b9e6619",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "prefix": "8",
      "metadata": {
        "createdAt": 1768038036243,
        "updatedAt": 1768038036243
      }
    },
    "f75c2fff-10f4-4fae-9051-1362cd9c4692": {
      "id": "f75c2fff-10f4-4fae-9051-1362cd9c4692",
      "name": "Conclusion",
      "content": "This plan transforms IdiamPro into an AI-native platform with full API access. The phased approach enables iterative development, early feedback, and risk mitigation. Open source core + paid premium balances community building with sustainable revenue.\n\n**Success Factors:**\n1. Developer experience (easy setup, great docs)\n2. Reliability (stable API, graceful errors)\n3. Performance (fast responses, efficient bulk ops)\n4. Security (robust auth, plan enforcement)\n5. Community (active engagement, contributions)",
      "type": "note",
      "parentId": "0b4b1874-027a-4b81-9918-1c126b9e6619",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "prefix": "12",
      "metadata": {
        "createdAt": 1768038036243,
        "updatedAt": 1768038036243
      }
    },
    "mcp-user-guide-section": {
      "id": "mcp-user-guide-section",
      "name": "User Guide \u2014 MCP for Non-Technical Users",
      "content": "<p><strong>Customer-facing content</strong> explaining MCP in plain language. This section can be exported as a website for marketing and user onboarding.</p>",
      "childrenIds": [
        "mcp-what",
        "mcp-capabilities",
        "mcp-getting-started",
        "mcp-how-works",
        "mcp-pricing",
        "mcp-scenarios",
        "mcp-faq"
      ],
      "isExpanded": true,
      "prefix": "9"
    },
    "mcp-what": {
      "id": "mcp-what",
      "name": "What is MCP?",
      "content": "<p><strong>MCP stands for Model Context Protocol.</strong> Think of it as a universal language that lets AI assistants talk to your apps.</p><p></p><p>Today, when you want an AI to help with your outlines, you have to copy text from IdiamPro, paste it into the AI chat, get the response, then paste it back. It's tedious and error-prone.</p><p></p><p><strong>With MCP, all of that disappears.</strong> Your AI assistant connects directly to IdiamPro. It can see your outlines, understand their structure, and make changes \u2014 all while you have a natural conversation.</p><p></p><p>It's like giving your AI assistant a set of keys to your knowledge library, with rules about what it can and can't do.</p>",
      "childrenIds": [
        "mcp-analogy",
        "mcp-who-made"
      ],
      "isExpanded": true,
      "prefix": "9.1"
    },
    "mcp-analogy": {
      "id": "mcp-analogy",
      "name": "A Simple Analogy",
      "content": "<p>Imagine hiring a research assistant. Without MCP, your assistant sits in a separate room. You have to walk over, hand them documents, wait for them to work, then walk back to pick up the results.</p><p></p><p><strong>With MCP, your assistant sits right next to you.</strong> They can reach into your filing cabinet, pull out what they need, do the work, and file the results \u2014 all while you're having a conversation about what you want.</p><p></p><p>That's what MCP does for IdiamPro. Your AI becomes a true collaborator, not just a separate tool.</p>",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isExpanded": true,
      "prefix": "9.1.1"
    },
    "mcp-who-made": {
      "id": "mcp-who-made",
      "name": "Who Created MCP?",
      "content": "<p>MCP was developed by <strong>Anthropic</strong>, the makers of Claude. It's an open standard, which means any AI assistant or app can use it. Think of it like USB \u2014 a universal connector that just works, no matter who made the device.</p><p></p><p>Major AI companies and thousands of developers have adopted MCP, making it the emerging standard for AI-to-app communication.</p>",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isExpanded": true,
      "prefix": "9.1.2"
    },
    "mcp-capabilities": {
      "id": "mcp-capabilities",
      "name": "What Can You Do With MCP + IdiamPro?",
      "content": "<p>Here are real examples of what becomes possible when your AI assistant can work directly with your outlines:</p>",
      "childrenIds": [
        "mcp-use-research",
        "mcp-use-organize",
        "mcp-use-generate",
        "mcp-use-daily"
      ],
      "isExpanded": true,
      "prefix": "9.2"
    },
    "mcp-use-research": {
      "id": "mcp-use-research",
      "name": "Research & Knowledge Building",
      "content": "<p><strong>\"Claude, research the latest developments in renewable energy and add them to my Energy Policy outline.\"</strong></p><p></p><p>Your AI assistant will:</p><ul><li><p>Search for current information</p></li><li><p>Create new nodes organized by topic</p></li><li><p>Add detailed content with citations</p></li><li><p>Tag everything appropriately</p></li><li><p>Place it in the right section of your existing outline</p></li></ul><p></p><p>What used to take hours of copy-pasting happens in minutes.</p>",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isExpanded": true,
      "prefix": "9.2.1"
    },
    "mcp-use-organize": {
      "id": "mcp-use-organize",
      "name": "Organization & Restructuring",
      "content": "<p><strong>\"Claude, my thesis outline is getting messy. Can you reorganize the methodology section and move the literature review references to a separate section?\"</strong></p><p></p><p>Your AI understands the hierarchy of your outline and can:</p><ul><li><p>Move nodes between sections</p></li><li><p>Create new parent categories</p></li><li><p>Merge duplicate content</p></li><li><p>Split oversized sections</p></li><li><p>Reorder items logically</p></li></ul>",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isExpanded": true,
      "prefix": "9.2.2"
    },
    "mcp-use-generate": {
      "id": "mcp-use-generate",
      "name": "Content Generation",
      "content": "<p><strong>\"Claude, I have an outline for my marketing plan but the sections are empty. Can you generate detailed content for each section?\"</strong></p><p></p><p>Your AI reads each node title, understands the context from the outline structure, and generates rich, relevant content \u2014 complete with formatting, bullet points, and even diagrams where helpful.</p>",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isExpanded": true,
      "prefix": "9.2.3"
    },
    "mcp-use-daily": {
      "id": "mcp-use-daily",
      "name": "Daily Workflows",
      "content": "<p>Some everyday examples:</p><p></p><ul><li><p><strong>Meeting notes:</strong> \"Claude, create an outline from today's meeting and add action items under each person's name.\"</p></li><li><p><strong>Project tracking:</strong> \"What's the status of all items tagged 'urgent' across my project outlines?\"</p></li><li><p><strong>Study prep:</strong> \"Create a study guide from my Biology lecture notes, organized by exam topic.\"</p></li><li><p><strong>Report writing:</strong> \"Draft an executive summary based on my quarterly review outline.\"</p></li><li><p><strong>Knowledge synthesis:</strong> \"Compare what I have in my AI Ethics outline with my Technology Policy outline and find gaps.\"</p></li></ul>",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isExpanded": true,
      "prefix": "9.2.4"
    },
    "mcp-getting-started": {
      "id": "mcp-getting-started",
      "name": "How to Get Started",
      "content": "<p>Setting up MCP with IdiamPro is straightforward. Here's what you need:</p>",
      "childrenIds": [
        "mcp-requirements",
        "mcp-setup-steps",
        "mcp-first-try"
      ],
      "isExpanded": true,
      "prefix": "9.3"
    },
    "mcp-requirements": {
      "id": "mcp-requirements",
      "name": "What You Need",
      "content": "<p><strong>1. IdiamPro</strong> \u2014 installed on your Mac, iPad, or iPhone</p><p><strong>2. Claude Desktop</strong> \u2014 Anthropic's desktop app (free with a Claude subscription)</p><p><strong>3. An API key</strong> \u2014 generated from IdiamPro's Settings page</p><p></p><p>That's it. No programming knowledge required. No terminal commands. No configuration files to edit.</p>",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isExpanded": true,
      "prefix": "9.3.1"
    },
    "mcp-setup-steps": {
      "id": "mcp-setup-steps",
      "name": "Setup Steps",
      "content": "<p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Open IdiamPro and go to Settings \u2192 Developer \u2192 Generate API Key</p><p></p><p><strong>Step 2:</strong> Open Claude Desktop and go to Settings \u2192 MCP Servers \u2192 Add Server</p><p></p><p><strong>Step 3:</strong> Select \"IdiamPro\" from the available servers and paste your API key</p><p></p><p><strong>Step 4:</strong> Start a conversation with Claude and mention your outlines \u2014 Claude now has access!</p><p></p><p>The connection is secure and private. Claude can only access your outlines through the MCP server \u2014 it can't see your files, emails, or anything else on your computer.</p>",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isExpanded": true,
      "prefix": "9.3.2"
    },
    "mcp-first-try": {
      "id": "mcp-first-try",
      "name": "Your First MCP Conversation",
      "content": "<p>Once connected, try saying something like:</p><p></p><p><em>\"Claude, can you show me a list of all my outlines in IdiamPro?\"</em></p><p></p><p>Claude will use the MCP connection to retrieve your outline list and display it. From there, you can ask it to open specific outlines, search for content, or start building something new.</p><p></p><p>It's as natural as talking to a knowledgeable colleague who happens to have perfect memory of everything in your outlines.</p>",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isExpanded": true,
      "prefix": "9.3.3"
    },
    "mcp-how-works": {
      "id": "mcp-how-works",
      "name": "How It Works Behind the Scenes",
      "content": "<p>You don't need to understand the technical details to use MCP, but here's a simple overview for the curious:</p>",
      "childrenIds": [
        "mcp-flow",
        "mcp-security",
        "mcp-tools-available"
      ],
      "isExpanded": true,
      "prefix": "9.4"
    },
    "mcp-flow": {
      "id": "mcp-flow",
      "name": "The Conversation Flow",
      "content": "<p>When you talk to Claude about your outlines, here's what happens:</p><p></p><ol><li><p><strong>You speak naturally</strong> \u2014 \"Find all my notes about machine learning\"</p></li><li><p><strong>Claude understands your intent</strong> \u2014 It knows you want to search your outlines</p></li><li><p><strong>Claude uses the MCP tool</strong> \u2014 It calls IdiamPro's search function automatically</p></li><li><p><strong>IdiamPro responds</strong> \u2014 It sends back the matching nodes and content</p></li><li><p><strong>Claude presents the results</strong> \u2014 In a clear, conversational format</p></li></ol><p></p><p>All of this happens in seconds, seamlessly, within your conversation.</p>",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isExpanded": true,
      "prefix": "9.4.1"
    },
    "mcp-security": {
      "id": "mcp-security",
      "name": "Security & Privacy",
      "content": "<p>Your data stays safe:</p><p></p><ul><li><p><strong>Local first:</strong> Your outlines are stored on your device, not in the cloud</p></li><li><p><strong>Controlled access:</strong> The MCP server only exposes the functions you authorize</p></li><li><p><strong>API key protection:</strong> You can revoke access at any time from Settings</p></li><li><p><strong>No data mining:</strong> IdiamPro never shares your outline data with third parties</p></li><li><p><strong>Encrypted connection:</strong> All communication between Claude and IdiamPro is encrypted</p></li></ul>",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isExpanded": true,
      "prefix": "9.4.2"
    },
    "mcp-tools-available": {
      "id": "mcp-tools-available",
      "name": "What Your AI Can Do (The MCP Tools)",
      "content": "<p>The MCP server gives your AI assistant specific capabilities, organized like permissions:</p><p></p><p><strong>Reading (always available):</strong></p><ul><li><p>List all your outlines</p></li><li><p>Open and read any outline</p></li><li><p>Search across all content</p></li><li><p>View tags and organization</p></li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Writing (always available):</strong></p><ul><li><p>Create new nodes and sections</p></li><li><p>Edit existing content</p></li><li><p>Move and reorganize nodes</p></li><li><p>Add and manage tags</p></li></ul><p></p><p><strong>AI-Powered (Premium):</strong></p><ul><li><p>Generate entire outlines from a topic</p></li><li><p>Expand content with AI-written text</p></li><li><p>Import and synthesize external sources</p></li><li><p>Bulk operations across many nodes</p></li></ul>",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isExpanded": true,
      "prefix": "9.4.3"
    },
    "mcp-pricing": {
      "id": "mcp-pricing",
      "name": "Plans & Pricing",
      "content": "<p>MCP access is included with your IdiamPro subscription, with different tiers for different needs:</p>",
      "childrenIds": [
        "mcp-free",
        "mcp-premium",
        "mcp-pro"
      ],
      "isExpanded": true,
      "prefix": "9.5"
    },
    "mcp-free": {
      "id": "mcp-free",
      "name": "Free Plan",
      "content": "<p><strong>$0/month \u2014 1,000 MCP operations/month</strong></p><p></p><p>Perfect for getting started and personal use:</p><ul><li><p>Read and search all your outlines</p></li><li><p>Create, edit, and organize nodes</p></li><li><p>Tag management</p></li><li><p>Works with Claude Desktop and other MCP clients</p></li></ul><p></p><p>1,000 operations is enough for casual daily use \u2014 roughly 30+ interactions per day.</p>",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isExpanded": true,
      "prefix": "9.5.1"
    },
    "mcp-premium": {
      "id": "mcp-premium",
      "name": "Premium Plan",
      "content": "<p><strong>$19/month \u2014 10,000 MCP operations/month</strong></p><p></p><p>For professionals and power users:</p><ul><li><p>Everything in Free</p></li><li><p>AI-powered outline generation (100/month)</p></li><li><p>AI content expansion (500/month)</p></li><li><p>Source ingestion \u2014 import from YouTube, PDFs, web pages (50/month)</p></li><li><p>Bulk operations on multiple nodes at once</p></li></ul>",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isExpanded": true,
      "prefix": "9.5.2"
    },
    "mcp-pro": {
      "id": "mcp-pro",
      "name": "Pro Plan",
      "content": "<p><strong>$49/month \u2014 50,000 MCP operations/month</strong></p><p></p><p>For researchers, teams, and heavy users:</p><ul><li><p>Everything in Premium</p></li><li><p>Unlimited AI operations</p></li><li><p>Semantic search \u2014 find content by meaning, not just keywords</p></li><li><p>Cross-outline queries \u2014 search and connect ideas across all your work</p></li><li><p>Priority support</p></li></ul>",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isExpanded": true,
      "prefix": "9.5.3"
    },
    "mcp-scenarios": {
      "id": "mcp-scenarios",
      "name": "Real-World Scenarios",
      "content": "<p>Here's how different professionals use MCP with IdiamPro every day:</p>",
      "childrenIds": [
        "mcp-scenario-student",
        "mcp-scenario-consultant",
        "mcp-scenario-writer"
      ],
      "isExpanded": true,
      "prefix": "9.6"
    },
    "mcp-scenario-student": {
      "id": "mcp-scenario-student",
      "name": "The Graduate Student",
      "content": "<p><strong>Sarah</strong> is writing her dissertation on climate policy. She has 47 research sources to synthesize.</p><p></p><p><em>\"Claude, I just uploaded three new PDFs about carbon pricing. Can you add the key findings to my Literature Review outline and tag them by methodology type?\"</em></p><p></p><p>In minutes, Claude ingests all three papers, extracts key findings, creates properly structured nodes in her outline, and tags them as 'quantitative', 'qualitative', or 'mixed methods'. What would have taken Sarah an afternoon happens while she grabs coffee.</p>",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isExpanded": true,
      "prefix": "9.6.1"
    },
    "mcp-scenario-consultant": {
      "id": "mcp-scenario-consultant",
      "name": "The Management Consultant",
      "content": "<p><strong>Marcus</strong> prepares client presentations every week from multiple data sources.</p><p></p><p><em>\"Claude, pull the key metrics from my Q3 Analysis outline and create an executive summary outline with recommendations prioritized by impact.\"</em></p><p></p><p>Claude reads through his detailed analysis, identifies the most important findings, creates a new outline structured for a board presentation, and highlights the top three recommendations. Marcus reviews, tweaks a few things, and exports it as a polished website to share with the client.</p>",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isExpanded": true,
      "prefix": "9.6.2"
    },
    "mcp-scenario-writer": {
      "id": "mcp-scenario-writer",
      "name": "The Non-Fiction Author",
      "content": "<p><strong>Elena</strong> is writing a book about the history of artificial intelligence.</p><p></p><p><em>\"Claude, I've been adding interview notes to my book outline all week. Can you review chapters 3 through 5 and identify any gaps in my narrative? Also suggest where I might need additional sources.\"</em></p><p></p><p>Claude analyzes the structure and content of three chapters, identifies that the transition from expert systems to machine learning lacks a key historical event, suggests two specific areas that need supporting sources, and even creates placeholder nodes where the new content should go.</p>",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isExpanded": true,
      "prefix": "9.6.3"
    },
    "mcp-faq": {
      "id": "mcp-faq",
      "name": "Frequently Asked Questions",
      "content": "<p>Common questions about MCP and IdiamPro:</p>",
      "childrenIds": [
        "mcp-faq-1",
        "mcp-faq-2",
        "mcp-faq-3",
        "mcp-faq-4",
        "mcp-faq-5",
        "mcp-faq-6"
      ],
      "isExpanded": true,
      "prefix": "9.7"
    },
    "mcp-faq-1": {
      "id": "mcp-faq-1",
      "name": "Do I need to know how to code?",
      "content": "<p><strong>No.</strong> MCP is designed so you interact entirely through natural conversation. You talk to Claude in plain English (or any language), and Claude handles all the technical communication with IdiamPro. You never see code, commands, or technical details.</p>",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isExpanded": true,
      "prefix": "9.7.1"
    },
    "mcp-faq-2": {
      "id": "mcp-faq-2",
      "name": "Is my data safe?",
      "content": "<p><strong>Yes.</strong> Your outlines stay on your device. The MCP connection only allows Claude to access your outlines through specific, controlled functions \u2014 it can't access your files, photos, emails, or anything else. You can revoke access instantly from Settings.</p>",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isExpanded": true,
      "prefix": "9.7.2"
    },
    "mcp-faq-3": {
      "id": "mcp-faq-3",
      "name": "Does it work with AI assistants other than Claude?",
      "content": "<p><strong>Yes.</strong> MCP is an open standard. While we've optimized the experience for Claude Desktop, any AI assistant that supports MCP can connect to IdiamPro. As more AI tools adopt MCP, your IdiamPro outlines become accessible to all of them.</p>",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isExpanded": true,
      "prefix": "9.7.3"
    },
    "mcp-faq-4": {
      "id": "mcp-faq-4",
      "name": "Can the AI accidentally delete my work?",
      "content": "<p><strong>Your work is protected.</strong> IdiamPro maintains undo history and automatic backups. If an AI operation produces unexpected results, you can undo it immediately. Destructive operations (like deleting large sections) require explicit confirmation.</p>",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isExpanded": true,
      "prefix": "9.7.4"
    },
    "mcp-faq-5": {
      "id": "mcp-faq-5",
      "name": "Does it work on my iPad and iPhone too?",
      "content": "<p><strong>Yes.</strong> The MCP server works with your IdiamPro data regardless of which device you're using. Changes made through MCP sync across all your devices, just like any other changes to your outlines.</p>",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isExpanded": true,
      "prefix": "9.7.5"
    },
    "mcp-faq-6": {
      "id": "mcp-faq-6",
      "name": "What's the difference between IdiamPro's built-in AI and MCP?",
      "content": "<p><strong>Built-in AI</strong> is the AI features inside IdiamPro itself \u2014 the Generate Content button, the AI menu, the Knowledge Chat. These work within the app's interface.</p><p></p><p><strong>MCP</strong> extends this by letting external AI assistants (like Claude Desktop) work with your outlines from outside the app. It's like the difference between using a calculator app vs. telling your assistant to run the numbers for you.</p><p></p><p>They complement each other. Use built-in AI for quick in-app tasks, and MCP for complex, multi-step workflows where conversation is more natural.</p>",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isExpanded": true,
      "prefix": "9.7.6"
    },
    "mcp-setup-guide": {
      "id": "mcp-setup-guide",
      "name": "Setup & Usage Guide",
      "content": "<p><strong>How to install, configure, and use the IdiamPro MCP Server.</strong></p>",
      "childrenIds": [
        "mcp-install",
        "mcp-claude-config",
        "mcp-tools-ref",
        "mcp-examples",
        "mcp-custom-dir"
      ],
      "isExpanded": true,
      "prefix": "10"
    },
    "mcp-install": {
      "id": "mcp-install",
      "name": "Installation",
      "content": "<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Node.js 18 or later</p></li><li><p>IdiamPro installed with outlines in ~/Documents/IDM Outlines/</p></li><li><p>Claude Desktop (for AI assistant integration)</p></li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Install from the project:</strong></p><ol><li><p>Navigate to the mcp-server directory inside the IdiamPro project</p></li><li><p>Run npm install to install dependencies</p></li><li><p>Run npm run build to compile the server</p></li></ol><p></p><p><strong>Verify it works:</strong></p><p>Run npm run dev \u2014 you should see \"Starting server v0.1.0\" and \"Server connected via stdio\" in the output.</p>",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isExpanded": true,
      "prefix": "10.1"
    },
    "mcp-claude-config": {
      "id": "mcp-claude-config",
      "name": "Connecting to Claude Desktop",
      "content": "<p>To connect the MCP server to Claude Desktop:</p><p></p><ol><li><p>Open Claude Desktop</p></li><li><p>Go to <strong>Settings \u2192 Developer \u2192 MCP Servers</strong></p></li><li><p>Click <strong>Add Server</strong></p></li><li><p>Set the server name to <strong>idiampro</strong></p></li><li><p>Set the command to: <strong>node</strong></p></li><li><p>Set the arguments to the full path of the compiled server, for example: <strong>/path/to/IdiamPro/mcp-server/dist/index.js</strong></p></li><li><p>Save and restart Claude Desktop</p></li></ol><p></p><p>Claude will now have access to all your IdiamPro outlines. You can verify by asking Claude: <em>\"Can you list my IdiamPro outlines?\"</em></p>",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isExpanded": true,
      "prefix": "10.2"
    },
    "mcp-tools-ref": {
      "id": "mcp-tools-ref",
      "name": "Available Tools Reference",
      "content": "<p><strong>12 tools are available in the free tier:</strong></p><p></p><p><strong>Read Operations:</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>list_outlines</strong> \u2014 List all outlines with name, file, node count, last modified date</p></li><li><p><strong>get_outline</strong> \u2014 Get the full structure of an outline including all nodes</p></li><li><p><strong>get_node</strong> \u2014 Get a specific node by ID with its content</p></li><li><p><strong>search_nodes</strong> \u2014 Search across outlines by node name or content</p></li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Write Operations:</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>create_node</strong> \u2014 Create a new node under a parent, with optional position</p></li><li><p><strong>update_node</strong> \u2014 Update a node's name and/or content</p></li><li><p><strong>delete_node</strong> \u2014 Delete a node and all its children</p></li><li><p><strong>move_node</strong> \u2014 Move a node to a different parent</p></li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Tag Operations:</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>add_tag</strong> \u2014 Add a tag to a node</p></li><li><p><strong>remove_tag</strong> \u2014 Remove a tag from a node</p></li><li><p><strong>list_tags</strong> \u2014 List all unique tags across outlines</p></li><li><p><strong>filter_by_tags</strong> \u2014 Find all nodes matching specific tags</p></li></ul>",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isExpanded": true,
      "prefix": "10.3"
    },
    "mcp-examples": {
      "id": "mcp-examples",
      "name": "Example Conversations with Claude",
      "content": "<p>Once connected, you can have natural conversations like these:</p><p></p><p><strong>Exploring your outlines:</strong></p><ul><li><p><em>\"List all my outlines in IdiamPro\"</em></p></li><li><p><em>\"Open my Development outline and show me the top-level sections\"</em></p></li><li><p><em>\"Search all my outlines for anything about TestFlight\"</em></p></li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Creating and organizing:</strong></p><ul><li><p><em>\"Create a new section called 'Q2 Goals' in my Business Development outline\"</em></p></li><li><p><em>\"Move the 'Pricing' section from my Planning outline to the Marketing outline\"</em></p></li><li><p><em>\"Add the tag 'urgent' to all nodes in my Bootstrap Plan that mention deadlines\"</em></p></li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Research and content:</strong></p><ul><li><p><em>\"Find all nodes tagged 'todo' across my project outlines and give me a summary\"</em></p></li><li><p><em>\"What does my MCP plan say about pricing tiers?\"</em></p></li><li><p><em>\"Create an outline node summarizing the key decisions we've made about compliance\"</em></p></li></ul>",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isExpanded": true,
      "prefix": "10.4"
    },
    "mcp-custom-dir": {
      "id": "mcp-custom-dir",
      "name": "Using a Custom Outlines Directory",
      "content": "<p>By default, the server looks for outlines in <strong>~/Documents/IDM Outlines/</strong>. To use a different directory, pass the --outlines-dir flag when starting the server:</p><p></p><p>In your Claude Desktop MCP configuration, add the flag to the arguments list. For example, if your outlines are in ~/MyOutlines, add <strong>--outlines-dir</strong> followed by the full path.</p><p></p><p>This is useful if you keep outlines in a different location or want to test with a separate set of files.</p>",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isExpanded": true,
      "prefix": "10.5"
    },
    "7adf45bf-bf03-4296-996e-26494b9e5fd7": {
      "id": "7adf45bf-bf03-4296-996e-26494b9e5fd7",
      "name": "MCP Server Test Procedures",
      "content": "Real-world workflow tests that exercise every MCP server feature. Run these after any code changes to the mcp-server/ directory. All tests assume the server is built (<code>npm run build</code>) and outlines exist in <code>~/Documents/IDM Outlines/</code>.",
      "type": "chapter",
      "parentId": "0b4b1874-027a-4b81-9918-1c126b9e6619",
      "childrenIds": [
        "3ec8cfbc-6ee5-4cd4-a0db-932c3b2165c4",
        "448d1eba-f04d-4868-a821-22c351081dda",
        "4be8a226-6fa2-4053-91c5-b786552c72d1",
        "efa1b176-4df4-4451-8281-a85add62899e",
        "55bdade7-11c3-4447-807f-e7bf0cfe7e20",
        "f6b702b8-7479-4673-ac26-5565238a97ed",
        "fa79229e-f693-4acf-aa53-178651dfafca",
        "7cd4c0ca-2d6f-4524-958f-829c19b1d31e"
      ],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "11"
    },
    "3ec8cfbc-6ee5-4cd4-a0db-932c3b2165c4": {
      "id": "3ec8cfbc-6ee5-4cd4-a0db-932c3b2165c4",
      "name": "Test 1: Server Startup & Connection",
      "content": "<strong>Purpose:</strong> Verify the server starts, connects, and registers all tools.\n\n<strong>Steps:</strong>\n1. Navigate to mcp-server/ directory\n2. Run <code>npm run build</code> \u2014 should complete with no errors\n3. Send an MCP initialize message via stdio\n4. Send a tools/list request\n5. Verify the response contains exactly 16 tools\n\n<strong>Expected:</strong>\n\u2022 Server logs \"Starting server v0.1.0\" to stderr\n\u2022 Server logs the outlines directory path\n\u2022 tools/list returns: list_outlines, get_outline, get_node, search_nodes, create_outline, create_node, update_node, delete_node, move_node, add_tag, remove_tag, list_tags, filter_by_tags, export_outline, generate_api_key, list_api_keys, revoke_api_key\n\n<strong>Status:</strong> \u2705 Passing (verified 2026-04-03)",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "7adf45bf-bf03-4296-996e-26494b9e5fd7",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "11.1"
    },
    "448d1eba-f04d-4868-a821-22c351081dda": {
      "id": "448d1eba-f04d-4868-a821-22c351081dda",
      "name": "Test 2: Read Operations",
      "content": "<strong>Purpose:</strong> Verify all read tools return correct data.\n\n<strong>Test 2a \u2014 list_outlines:</strong>\n1. Call list_outlines with no arguments\n2. Verify it returns an array of outline summaries\n3. Each entry should have: id, name, fileName, nodeCount, lastModified\n4. Verify at least your known outlines appear\n\n<strong>Test 2b \u2014 get_outline:</strong>\n1. Pick a known outline file name from the list\n2. Call get_outline with that fileName\n3. Verify it returns: id, name, rootNodeId, nodes (object)\n4. Verify rootNodeId exists in nodes\n\n<strong>Test 2c \u2014 get_node:</strong>\n1. From the outline above, pick a node ID\n2. Call get_node with fileName and nodeId\n3. Verify it returns the node with: id, name, content, type, parentId, childrenIds\n\n<strong>Test 2d \u2014 search_nodes:</strong>\n1. Call search_nodes with query \"marketing\" (or any term you know exists)\n2. Verify results include fileName, outlineName, nodeId, nodeName, matchContext, matchField\n3. Test with searchNames: false to verify content-only search\n4. Test with a specific fileName to verify single-outline search\n5. Test with a query that matches nothing \u2014 should return empty array\n\n<strong>Status:</strong> \u2705 Passing (verified 2026-04-03)",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "7adf45bf-bf03-4296-996e-26494b9e5fd7",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "11.2"
    },
    "4be8a226-6fa2-4053-91c5-b786552c72d1": {
      "id": "4be8a226-6fa2-4053-91c5-b786552c72d1",
      "name": "Test 3: Write Operations",
      "content": "<strong>Purpose:</strong> Verify outline and node creation, updates, moves, and deletes.\n\n<strong>Test 3a \u2014 create_outline:</strong>\n1. Call create_outline with name: \"MCP Test Outline\"\n2. Verify response has success: true, fileName, outlineId, rootNodeId\n3. Call list_outlines \u2014 verify the new outline appears\n4. Call get_outline on it \u2014 verify it has a root node with the correct name\n\n<strong>Test 3b \u2014 create_node:</strong>\n1. Call create_node on the test outline with parentId = rootNodeId, name = \"First Node\"\n2. Verify response has success: true and a new nodeId\n3. Call get_outline \u2014 verify root now has the child\n4. Create a second node with position: 0 \u2014 verify it appears before the first\n\n<strong>Test 3c \u2014 update_node:</strong>\n1. Call update_node with the first node's ID, new name: \"Updated Node\"\n2. Call get_node \u2014 verify name changed\n3. Call update_node with content: \"<p>Hello world</p>\" \u2014 verify content updated\n\n<strong>Test 3d \u2014 move_node:</strong>\n1. Create a third node under root\n2. Call move_node to move it under the first node\n3. Call get_outline \u2014 verify the node's parentId changed and parent's childrenIds updated\n\n<strong>Test 3e \u2014 delete_node:</strong>\n1. Call delete_node on the first node (which now has a child)\n2. Verify both the node and its descendant are deleted\n3. Call get_outline \u2014 verify they're gone\n\n<strong>Cleanup:</strong> Delete the test outline file from ~/Documents/IDM Outlines/\n\n<strong>Status:</strong> \u2b1c Not yet run manually",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "7adf45bf-bf03-4296-996e-26494b9e5fd7",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "11.3"
    },
    "efa1b176-4df4-4451-8281-a85add62899e": {
      "id": "efa1b176-4df4-4451-8281-a85add62899e",
      "name": "Test 4: Tag Operations",
      "content": "<strong>Purpose:</strong> Verify tag add/remove/list/filter across outlines.\n\n<strong>Test 4a \u2014 add_tag:</strong>\n1. Create a test outline with 3 nodes\n2. Call add_tag on node 1 with tag: \"important\"\n3. Call add_tag on node 2 with tag: \"important\" and tag: \"review\"\n4. Call get_node \u2014 verify metadata.tags contains the tags\n5. Call add_tag with an existing tag \u2014 should say \"Tag already exists\"\n\n<strong>Test 4b \u2014 list_tags:</strong>\n1. Call list_tags with no arguments \u2014 should return all unique tags\n2. Call list_tags with fileName \u2014 should return tags only from that outline\n3. Verify both \"important\" and \"review\" appear\n\n<strong>Test 4c \u2014 filter_by_tags:</strong>\n1. Call filter_by_tags with tags: [\"important\"] \u2014 should return nodes 1 and 2\n2. Call filter_by_tags with tags: [\"review\"] \u2014 should return only node 2\n3. Call filter_by_tags with tags: [\"important\", \"review\"] \u2014 should return both (OR logic)\n\n<strong>Test 4d \u2014 remove_tag:</strong>\n1. Call remove_tag on node 1 with tag: \"important\"\n2. Call get_node \u2014 verify tag is gone\n3. Call remove_tag with a non-existent tag \u2014 should succeed gracefully\n\n<strong>Cleanup:</strong> Delete test outline\n\n<strong>Status:</strong> \u2b1c Not yet run manually",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "7adf45bf-bf03-4296-996e-26494b9e5fd7",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "11.4"
    },
    "55bdade7-11c3-4447-807f-e7bf0cfe7e20": {
      "id": "55bdade7-11c3-4447-807f-e7bf0cfe7e20",
      "name": "Test 5: Export Operations",
      "content": "<strong>Purpose:</strong> Verify Markdown and text export with full outline and subtree.\n\n<strong>Test 5a \u2014 Markdown export:</strong>\n1. Call export_outline with a known outline and format: \"markdown\"\n2. Verify output starts with # (heading) for root node name\n3. Verify child nodes appear as ## headings\n4. Verify content appears as plain text (HTML stripped)\n5. Verify hierarchical indentation is correct\n\n<strong>Test 5b \u2014 Text export:</strong>\n1. Call export_outline with format: \"text\"\n2. Verify output uses indentation (no markdown heading syntax)\n3. Verify all nodes appear with proper nesting\n\n<strong>Test 5c \u2014 Subtree export:</strong>\n1. Call export_outline with a specific nodeId (not root)\n2. Verify only that subtree is exported\n3. Verify the starting node is the top-level heading\n\n<strong>Test 5d \u2014 Non-existent outline:</strong>\n1. Call export_outline with a fake fileName\n2. Verify error response\n\n<strong>Status:</strong> \u2705 Passing (basic export verified 2026-04-03)",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "7adf45bf-bf03-4296-996e-26494b9e5fd7",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "11.5"
    },
    "f6b702b8-7479-4673-ac26-5565238a97ed": {
      "id": "f6b702b8-7479-4673-ac26-5565238a97ed",
      "name": "Test 6: API Key Management",
      "content": "<strong>Purpose:</strong> Verify key generation, listing, and revocation.\n\n<strong>Test 6a \u2014 generate_api_key:</strong>\n1. Call generate_api_key with name: \"Test Key\"\n2. Verify response has rawKey starting with \"idm_\", keyId, and success: true\n3. Verify the warning about saving the key is present\n4. Save the rawKey for later tests\n\n<strong>Test 6b \u2014 list_api_keys:</strong>\n1. Call list_api_keys\n2. Verify the test key appears with name, tier: \"free\", isActive: true\n3. Verify the keyHash is NOT returned (security)\n4. Generate a second key and verify both appear\n\n<strong>Test 6c \u2014 revoke_api_key:</strong>\n1. Call revoke_api_key with the first key's ID\n2. Verify success: true\n3. Call list_api_keys \u2014 verify isActive is now false for that key\n4. Call revoke_api_key with a fake ID \u2014 verify success: false\n\n<strong>Cleanup:</strong> Delete ~/.idiampro/api-keys.json\n\n<strong>Status:</strong> \u2705 Passing (key generation verified 2026-04-03)",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "7adf45bf-bf03-4296-996e-26494b9e5fd7",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "11.6"
    },
    "fa79229e-f693-4acf-aa53-178651dfafca": {
      "id": "fa79229e-f693-4acf-aa53-178651dfafca",
      "name": "Test 7: Edge Cases & Error Handling",
      "content": "<strong>Purpose:</strong> Verify the server handles bad input gracefully.\n\n<strong>Test 7a \u2014 Non-existent outline:</strong>\n1. Call get_outline with fileName: \"does-not-exist.idm\"\n2. Verify isError: true response\n\n<strong>Test 7b \u2014 Non-existent node:</strong>\n1. Call get_node with a valid outline but fake nodeId\n2. Verify isError: true\n\n<strong>Test 7c \u2014 Delete root node:</strong>\n1. Call delete_node with the root node ID\n2. Verify error: \"Cannot delete the root node\"\n\n<strong>Test 7d \u2014 Move into own subtree:</strong>\n1. Create parent > child structure\n2. Call move_node trying to move parent under child\n3. Verify error: \"Cannot move a node into its own subtree\"\n\n<strong>Test 7e \u2014 Duplicate outline name:</strong>\n1. Create an outline\n2. Call create_outline with the same fileName\n3. Verify error: \"Outline already exists\"\n\n<strong>Test 7f \u2014 Empty search:</strong>\n1. Call search_nodes with query: \"xyzzy_no_match_12345\"\n2. Verify empty results array (not an error)\n\n<strong>Status:</strong> \u2b1c Not yet run manually",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "7adf45bf-bf03-4296-996e-26494b9e5fd7",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "11.7"
    },
    "7cd4c0ca-2d6f-4524-958f-829c19b1d31e": {
      "id": "7cd4c0ca-2d6f-4524-958f-829c19b1d31e",
      "name": "Test 8: Claude Desktop Integration",
      "content": "<strong>Purpose:</strong> End-to-end test with a real Claude Desktop connection.\n\n<strong>Prerequisites:</strong>\n\u2022 MCP server built (npm run build)\n\u2022 Claude Desktop config updated with idiampro server entry\n\u2022 Claude Desktop restarted\n\n<strong>Test 8a \u2014 Connection:</strong>\n1. Open Claude Desktop\n2. Look for \"idiampro\" in the MCP servers list (bottom of input area)\n3. Verify it shows as connected (green indicator)\n\n<strong>Test 8b \u2014 Natural language workflows:</strong>\nAsk Claude each of these and verify it calls the right tool:\n1. \"List all my outlines\" \u2192 should call list_outlines\n2. \"Search for anything about marketing across all outlines\" \u2192 should call search_nodes\n3. \"Show me the structure of my Business Plan outline\" \u2192 should call get_outline\n4. \"Create a new outline called Test from Claude\" \u2192 should call create_outline\n5. \"Add a node called Introduction under the root\" \u2192 should call create_node\n6. \"Export that outline as markdown\" \u2192 should call export_outline\n7. \"Tag the Introduction node with 'draft'\" \u2192 should call add_tag\n8. \"Delete the test outline\" \u2192 user should delete the file\n\n<strong>Test 8c \u2014 Error recovery:</strong>\n1. Ask Claude to get an outline that doesn't exist\n2. Verify Claude reports the error clearly\n3. Ask Claude to delete a root node\n4. Verify Claude reports the restriction\n\n<strong>Status:</strong> \u2b1c Not yet run",
      "type": "document",
      "parentId": "7adf45bf-bf03-4296-996e-26494b9e5fd7",
      "childrenIds": [],
      "isCollapsed": false,
      "prefix": "11.8"
    }
  },
